, xAI had acquired X (including X.AI Corp.). Twitter was acquired by Elon Musk in October 2022.\n*   **Transaction Structure:** Each merger was effected through a share exchange with specific conversion ratios (e.g., X Common Stock converted to 2.776 shares of xAI Common Stock).\n*   **Change in Reporting Entity:** The retrospective combination is explicitly described as a **"change in reporting entity"** under accounting standards.\n*   **Omission of Separate Financials:** Because the consolidated financials already reflect the combined entity retroactively, **separate financial statements for xAI and X are not provided**.\n\n### **3. What Historical Information is No Longer Observable / Standalone?**\n\nAs a result of the common-control accounting, **no financial data reflects the standalone operations of SpaceX prior to the mergers.** All historical financial information presented in the prospectus (including revenue, expenses, assets, liabilities, and shareholders\' equity for periods before 2025 and 2026) is the **consolidated result of SpaceX, xAI, and X combined.**\n\n*   **Impact on Comparability:** Investors cannot analyze SpaceX\'s standalone financial performance, margins, or capital structure before it absorbed xAI and X. The historical data is a blend of all three companies.\n*   **Capital Structure Presentation:** The capital stock and shareholders\' equity sections reflect the combined historical equity of all entities, adjusted for the merger exchange ratios and a subsequent 2026 stock split.\n\n### **4. Other Key Accounting Notes**\n\n*   **Stock Split:** A five-for-one forward stock split in May 2026 is reflected retroactively in all share and per-share data.\n*   **Redeemable Preferred Stock:** xAI\'s redeemable convertible preferred stock was converted to SpaceX Common Stock upon the xAI Merger, but its historical balance is presented as preferred stock until the conversion date (not recast retroactively as common stock).\n\nIn summary, the common-control accounting treatment means **the prospectus presents a historical financial view of the combined SpaceX/xAI/X entity from inception**, with assets at book value and no new acquisition-related accounting entries. This provides a cohesive historical record of the consolidated group but **obscures the separate financial history and standalone performance of SpaceX as it existed before these transformative mergers.**',
